NPA head Shaun Abrahams insists he did not bow to public pressure in making the about turn in Pravin Gordhan&#8217;s fraud case. JOHANNESBURG - National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) head Shaun Abrahams has told Eyewitness News he is not politically captured and he demonstrated his independence by withdrawing criminal charges against Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan.In an exclusive interview, the National Director of Public Prosecutions insists he did not bow to public pressure in making the about turn in the case against the minister.There's been a backlash against Abrahams following the debacle, with many calling on him to resign.Abrahams acknowledges he is public enemy number one but he insists he was not doing the bidding of any political powers by charging Gordhan. Never. Never at any stage and never will I be. I can assure the public out there and myself that that s certainly not the case. He believes his decision to withdraw the charges showed that he has not been influenced. Even though there s a massive political narrative out there associated with the matter, I hope my decision to withdraw the charges clearly demonstrated my independence. Abrahams says he does not want to play politics and will not allow the NPA to be pulled into a political quagmire.WATCH: Shaun Abrahams in the wake of the Gordhan charges